    • resetScene

      public void resetScene(javafx.event.ActionEvent actionEvent) throws IOException
      This method takes in the action event and passes it along with the runtime class of the current object to main.main.returnToMainMenu.
      Parameters:
      actionEvent - the action event passed in by clicking a button. It is used by main.Main.returnToMainMenu to recycle the current scene at the time this method was called.
      Throws:
      IOException - if the main.Main.returnToMainMenu method throws an IOException.
